<aura:component extends="auradocs:topicPanel">
       <aura:set attribute="title" value="aura:renderIf "/>

       <p>Renders the content within the tag if the <code>isTrue</code> attribute evaluates to true.</p>

       <p>
       <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
          <thead>
              <tr>
                     <td><b>Attribute Name</b></td>
                     <td><b>Type</b></td>
                     <td><b>Description</b></td>
                     <td><b>Required?</b></td>
              </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
              <tr>
                     <td><code>else</code></td>
                     <td>Component[]</td>
                     <td>The markup to render when <code>isTrue</code> evaluates to false. Set this attribute using the <code>aura:set</code> tag.</td>
                     <td></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                     <td><code>isTrue</code></td>
                     <td>String</td>
                     <td>An expression that determines whether the content is displayed. If it evaluates to true, the content is displayed.</td>
                     <td>Y</td>
              </tr>
          </tbody>
       </table>
       </p>

       <h2>Usage</h2>
       <p>The following components in the auradocs namespace show how to use <code>aura:renderIf</code> to conditionally render markup based on the result of evaluating an expression.</p>

       <p><b>sampleRender.cmp</b></p>

       <p>The <b>Component source</b> tab shows the markup for <code>sampleRender.cmp</code>, which extends <code>sampleRenderMe.cmp</code>.</p>

       <auradocs:example descriptor="auradocs:sampleRender" />

       <p>See the source for <code>sampleRenderMe.cmp</code> to understand the output.</p>

       <p><b>sampleRenderMe.cmp</b></p>

       <auradocs:example descriptor="auradocs:sampleRenderMe" />

        <p>The <code>aura:renderIf</code> component displays the  elements in the body
       only if the <code>desc</code> attribute contains a value.
       In other words, the content of the <code>aura:renderIf</code> component will be displayed if the
       <code>isTrue</code> attribute evaluates to true. The <code>desc</code> attribute is set in <code>sampleRender.cmp</code>, which extends <code>sampleRenderMe.cmp</code>.</p>

</aura:component>
